TY  - JOUR
T1  - How Similarity to Peers and Supervisor Influences Organizational Advancement in Different Cultures
AU  - Schaubroeck, John
AU  - Lam, Simon S. K.
Y1  - 2002/12/01
PY  - 2002
DA  - 2002/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/3069428
DO  - 10.5465/3069428
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1120
EP  - 1136
VL  - 45
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study tested hypotheses concerning how similarity of personality traits between promotion candidates and their peers and supervisors influences promotion decisions in different work unit cultures. Personality similarity to peers was positively associated with promotion in units with high individualism. In units with high collectivism, supervisor-subordinate personality similarity was instead a significant predictor of advancement. Behavioral integration between candidates and their peers and supervisors partially mediated the influence of personality similarity on promotion. Demographic similarity had little influence on promotion decisions. We discuss implications for understanding similarity effects and for increasing the validity of promotion decisions.
AB  - This study tested hypotheses concerning how similarity of personality traits between promotion candidates and their peers and supervisors influences promotion decisions in different work unit cultures. Personality similarity to peers was positively associated with promotion in units with high individualism. In units with high collectivism, supervisor-subordinate personality similarity was instead a significant predictor of advancement. Behavioral integration between candidates and their peers and supervisors partially mediated the influence of personality similarity on promotion. Demographic similarity had little influence on promotion decisions. We discuss implications for understanding similarity effects and for increasing the validity of promotion decisions.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/3069428
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/3069428
